        "id": 3135354,
        "name": "Don Cornutt",
        "username": "dcornutt",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dcornutt/{size}/562_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-03-31T22:35:07.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is such a stunning young wine.  It starts out with a little honeycomb and some elevage notes (wood). Lemon yellow fruit.   With air, the wine turns crystalline.  The nose is all seductive lemon yellow fruit.  Rich on the palate but lively.  The palate is mineral.  Incredibly long and it keeps evolving layers.  This is one of the best of the 2018 whites I have tasted from Burgundy.  Bravo!</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 9,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-04T03:25:05.763Z",
